                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>Two non adjacent fragments of a white <material>marble</material> sculpted panel depicting an architrave surmounted by a Doric frieze 
                                        with antefixes, possibly part of a <objectType>naiskos</objectType>; the left and right ends are lost; what remains is as follows:
                                        fragment a, broken off at left, right and below, has part of the metope number ii
                                        (<dimensions>
                                            <width>0.17</width>
                                            <height>0.135</height>
                                            <depth>0.05</depth>
                                        </dimensions>); 
                                        fragment b, broken off at right, has part of the frieze from metope iv to metope vii and the corresponding architrave, with a part missing
                                        at right
                                        (<dimensions>
                                            <width>0.44</width>
                                            <height>0.19</height>
                                            <depth>0.05</depth>
                                        </dimensions>);
                                        estimated width of the complete panel at least 0.95.</p>
                                </support>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> in one broken line within the metopes and in presumably four columns of 
                                    two lines each on the architrave below.</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><height>0.01</height>; no serifs, broad alpha, slanting mu and sigma, slightly dissymmetrical nu, smaller circular letters, open omega.</handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
